<TITLE> Govt approves 12 Ecnec projects </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, October 8 (bdnews24.com)  The government Monday decided to implement a Tk 1,474 crore integrated project to develop the Hatirjheel-Begunbari canal. The Executive Committee of the National Economic Council (Ecnec) in a meeting presided over by chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed approved 12 development projects, including the Hatirjheel-Begunbarhi project, at a cost of Tk 5,058 crore. Planning secretary Jafar Ahmed Chowdhury briefed reporters after the meeting. The secretary said Begunbari project will kick off during the FY 2006-07 and take nearly three and a half years to complete. The canal project has been envisaged to address flooding as well as waste water drainage problems of Dhaka City, he said. The approved projects also include the national agricultural technology phase 1 under the agriculture and fisheries and livestock ministries, and the systems loss reduction project under the energy ministry. bdnews24.
